This is a great article. Project Timaeus is such a creative idea, hell, the whole object is a such a creative idea. I love it.

One minor suggestion. In your author's note, you say that:



this is someone who gets around a week of human interaction per every couple thousand years.
附加记录：    

That is not the impression of the magnitude of the time distortion that I got at all. You don't specify how much the time is distorted by in the article, only saying that it's a  so I thought that time was sped up by 10x or 20x, but according to your note, you're trying to express that it's being sped up by like 50,000x. So, I would recommend that you give the multiplicative factor a range, similarly to how you specified a range between the distortions, or specify how much time -2 usually experiences per distortion.








